- how to run the service
- how to whitelist keys

issue.title: Improve dmsgpty
issue.body:
**Feature description**

Dmsgpty works well at the moment but it is a bit complicated to setup. We need to modify the bevaior in a few respects

- `dmsgpty-host` should default to production deployment `dmsg.discovery.skywire.skycoin.com` instead of `skywire.cc`
- `dmsgpty-host` should look for conf in `./config.json` by default and if no other path is specified
- `--skgen` should be deprecated. A new SecKey should be generated in all cases if a new conf is generated
- `--sk` should be deprecated. It should just be set via config file
- separate whitelisting files should be deprecated. The whitelisting values should be specified in config file
- `confpath` should be shortened to `-c`
- there is no need for an in memory whitelist. upon adding/removing whitelist items we should just flush to config

issue.title: Add constantsv2 benchmarking
issue.body:
Add these benchmarks

1. Program that tries to output number zero.
Score is square of how far number is from zero. But capped at int32 max. Dont let it overflow.
2. Program that tries to output 1. Same as above.
3. Program that tries to output 2.
4. Program that tries to output 7.
5. Program that tries to output random number from 0 to 256.

This is benchmark called "constantsv2"

issue.title: SpriteLoader
issue.body:
you can look at the code

1. Take array of sprite sheets

2. Load the .png into memory as bitmap for the list

3. Time how long it takes

4. Try wrapping each sprite load in a goroutine because the read will block

5. Time difference between serial read/load and doing them in parrallel in a goroutine

6. Have "read png" function

And check if png is already loaded to bitmap with a map, cache. And put filename in map if the file is already loaded or scheduled to be loaded

7. Have an integer id for the .png

---

The bitmap is slice with 4 bytes per pixel. RGBA

And has width in pixels and height in pixels. As a struct

Struct Bitmap_RGBA {
 Width int
Height int
pixels []byte
}


And time 
- how long to read file from disc
- how long to convert the .png to internal format

When we have 800 or 2000 sprite sheets, it will get slow. So need that for later.

To speed up level loading and startup time.

We load and process the spritesheet in background while game is starting or player is on intro screen.

---

Create /stats folder
- put the sprite loading stats in /stats module
- put timing/profiling code in stats module (startup time, total sprite loading time, etc)
